  • Classes in io.github.zachohara.bukkit.common.command used by io.github.zachohara.bukkit.common.command 
    Class and Description
    CommandExecutables
    The CommandExecutables interface is designed to be implemented by an enumeration class that represents the set of commands that a plugin supports.
    CommandInstance
    A CommandInstance object represents a single invocation of any command that is registered to a plugin.
    CommandRules
    The CommandRules interface is designed to be implemented by an enumeration class that represents the set of commands that a plugin supports.
    CommandRules.Source
    Represents the set of possible sources, or ranges of sources, that may be allowed to use any single command.
    CommandRules.Target
    Represents the set of possible targets, or ranges of targets, that may be allowed to be targeted by any single command.
    CommandRulesEntry
    A CommandRulesEntry object represents the rules and conditions for a command.
    Implementation
    The Implementation class acts as a superclass for implementations of specific commands.
